<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-402-312  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 402 312.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  June 26 1989 n544 pT28(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Linking design to test.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Faust, Mark; Noel, Vance.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The advent of computer-aided engineering (CAE) tools has extendedthe flexibility of designers and introduced an era of more complexproduct development.andP;  Such technological innovations ascomputer-integrated manufacturing (CIM), robot assembly andautomated inventory systems have made the manufacturing processmore efficient.andP;  The integration of design and testing and themanagement of behavioral data are necessary to make certain thatcompanies derive the full benefits from their designs.andP;  Thecomplexity of today's integrated circuits requires the flexibilityof such testing programs as Test Systems Strategies Inc's TestDevelopment Series (TDS), which provides an easily-used humaninterface for the merging and analysis of data from multiplesources.andP;  With TDS, users are able to check simulated circuitbehavior for compliance with design specifications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Test Systems Strategies Inc. (product development).andO;Product:   Test Development Series (Computer program) (product development).andO;Topic:     Computer-Aided EngineeringTestingProduct DevelopmentAutomationSoftware EngineeringIntegrated Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   CAD tools in the product development process. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>